  "text": "Racial disparities in breast cancer survival that demonstrate a significant disadvantage for black women have persisted, as relative gains have been made in improving breast cancer survival for other groups across the USA during 1990-2009 [CITATION_1] . This paper studies factors associated with Medicaideligible women's access to breast cancer screening from 2006 to 2008. An in-depth examination of differences among them in the odds of using mammography is provided, including both fee-for-service (FFS) and managed care Medicaid claims from 25 states with good quality data.",
